{
  "texts": [
    "It emphasizes key research trends, publication patterns across various countries and journals, author contributions and networks, and global collaborations in the application of AI for diagnosing and treating breast cancer.",
    "The United States has led the publication of research articles on AI for breast cancer diagnosis and treatment, with India and Spain also making significant contributions.",
    "Although the USA has the highest global influence based on total citation metrics, the Netherlands stands out in terms of average citations per article in this field.",
    "This may be due to Dutch research institutions are renowned for their focus on producing high-quality, impactful studies on AI rather than simply increasing publication volume.",
    "As an example, recently they have lay out the theoretical framework, purpose, and structure of a novel AI consortium cardiovascular artificial intelligence (AI) research namely CVON-AI consortium."
  ]
}